vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G6-U1-L15', "Students learn to visualize how a 2D net folds into a 3D shape and calculate surface area by summing all face areas. The critical misconceptions: faces arranged incorrectly on the net (overlapping or misoriented), forgetting to count all faces, and miscalculating triangle areas (applying base×height instead of ½·base×height). Success requires careful tracking of edge lengths between the 3D drawing and its net.").

