vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U1-L16', teacher, "Comprehend that surface area and volume are two different attributes of three-dimensional objects and are measured in different units").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U1-L16', teacher, "Describe (orally and in writing) shapes built out of cubes, including observations about their surface area and volume").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U1-L16', teacher, "Determine the surface area and volume of shapes made out of cubes").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U1-L16', student, "Let's contrast surface area and volume.").
vision_lesson_purpose('IM-G6-U1-L16', "This optional lesson reminds students of the distinctions between measures of one-, two-, and three-dimensional attributes. It reinforces that length is one-dimensional, surface area is two-dimensional, and volume is three-dimensional.").
