vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G6-U2-L2', "This lesson (6.RP.A.1) is about representing and interpreting ratios through discrete diagrams and ratio language; it deliberately precedes unit-rate and equivalent-ratio work — the narrative explicitly declines to write an association like 2:1 and defers equivalent ratios to later lessons. No addition, subtraction, or explicit multiplication is demanded. The only number-fill demands are partitive \"for every\" rate statements (one quantity shared into equal groups per unit of another), which fit fair_share_equal_groups rather than the first pass's measure_groups_of_size; both cool-down events w").

vision_lesson('IM-G6-U2-L3', 6, 2, 3, "Recipes").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U2-L3', teacher, "Draw and label a discrete diagram with circled groups to represent multiple batches of a recipe.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U2-L3', teacher, "Explain equivalent ratios (orally and in writing) in terms of different-sized batches of the same recipe having the same taste.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U2-L3', teacher, "Understand that doubling or tripling a recipe involves multiplying the amount of each ingredient by the same number, yielding something that tastes the same.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U2-L3', student, "Let's explore how ratios affect the way a recipe tastes.").
vision_lesson_purpose('IM-G6-U2-L3', "This is the first of two lessons that develop the idea of equivalent ratios through physical experiences. A key understanding is that if we scale a recipe up (or down) to make multiple batches (or a fraction of a batch), the result will still be the same in some meaningful way. In this lesson, students see this idea in the context of taste. A mixture containing two batches of a recipe tastes the same as a mixture containing one batch. The fact that two equivalent ratios yield the same taste is a physical manifestation of the equivalence of the ratios. Students notice structure when they see that scaling a recipe requires multiplying the amount of each ingredient by the same factor.").
vision_lesson_standard('IM-G6-U2-L3', addressing, '6.RP.A.1').
