vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G6-U3-L5', "Grade 6 ratio/rate lesson. Demanded operations are (a) dividing the two terms of a ratio to produce per-1 unit rates and (b) scaling a unit rate by a quantity. Unit-rate divisions are tagged scale_ratio_unit (the ratio-category automaton); the scaling-up steps are tagged repeat_equal_groups (multiplication). The 5.1 Math Talk opens with four true/false judgments about division/fraction/decimal equivalence (e.g., 5÷10=0.5); these demand division but no whole-number division automaton fits the mental fraction/decimal reasoning, so they are marked kind NONE. The third Math Talk statement, '4÷20=2").

