vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G6-U3-L7', "The optional Activity 7.3 includes metric-to-imperial conversions that chain multiple rates and so exceed the single-operation functor format: kangaroo 1,073 meters to feet and ostrich 1.15 kilometers to feet. Page 135 spells them out as (1,073) . 100 / 2.54 / 12 = 3,520.34 and (1.15) . (1,000) . 100 / 2.54 / 12 = 3,772.97 (m to cm to in to ft, with km to m for the ostrich). No measurement automaton captures a chained cross-system conversion in one step; these fall at the boundary where converting requires human judgment about which intermediate unit to route through. They are therefore exclud").

