vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G6-U3-L8', "Every computational task fits the arithmetic vocabulary; none demands an operation outside it, so there is no NONE. The lesson is a uniform divide-then-scale rate structure. Divisions that find a rate per 1 (or per equal part of a whole) are partitive and classified fair_share_equal_groups: 828/3 (meters per third of the climb), 138/4 (meters per quarter hour), 330/10 and 310/10 (feet per second), 33/4 (dollars per hour), 4/5 (dollars per can). This corrects the first pass, which split these structurally identical unit-rate divisions between fair_share_equal_groups and missing_factor_known_pro").

