vision_lesson('IM-G6-U3-L10', 6, 3, 10, "What Are Percentages?").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U3-L10', teacher, "Comprehend the word \"percentage\" (in written and spoken language) and the symbol \"%\" (in written language) to mean a rate per 100.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U3-L10', teacher, "Draw and label a double number line diagram to represent percentages of a dollar and to find corresponding monetary values or percentages.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U3-L10', student, "Let's learn about percentages.").
vision_lesson_purpose('IM-G6-U3-L10', "This lesson introduces percent and percentage. Students learn that percent means \"per hundred\" and describes the ratio of a quantity to 100. They begin with gridded 10-by-10 squares, each representing an area of 100 square units, and use \"percent of the large square\" to describe shaded regions (including values less than, equal to, and greater than 100). They then treat percentages as rates per 100 with money as the main context, expressing coin values as percentages of a dollar (100 cents), and use double number line diagrams to align dollar amounts with percentages and connect the idea to equivalent ratios. Here 100% corresponds only to 100 units of area and to 1 dollar; later lessons let 100% correspond to other values.").
