vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G6-U3-L10', "The lesson's conceptual core—percent as a rate per 100—is developed through coin values and double number line diagrams and does not demand arithmetic missing from the vocabulary; every extracted task is whole-number multiplication or addition of coin values, or a partitive division to find a unit price / a half. The genuine boundary is in the review problems that are NOT part of this lesson's content: Practice 5 (tokens) and Practice 6 (snail) demand multi-step proportional reasoning—first a unit-rate division ($4.40 / 8 = $0.55 per token; 10 cm / 4 min = 2.5 cm/min), then scaling ($6.05 / $0").

vision_lesson('IM-G6-U3-L11', 6, 3, 11, "Representing Percentages with Double Number Line Diagrams").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U3-L11', teacher, "Comprehend a phrase like \"A% of B\" (in written and spoken language) to refer to the value that makes a ratio with B that is equivalent to A : 100.").
