vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G6-U3-L11', "This lesson centers on percentages as multiplicative comparisons and ratios per 100. The core operations—finding P% of N and finding N when N is P% of M—are not represented by automata in the provided vocabulary, which derives from K–5 arithmetic strategies. Percentage-finding is conceptually distinct from earlier grade-level operations and involves understanding a percentage as a rate per 100 and scaling quantities proportionally. This marks a significant shift in mathematical reasoning introduced at Grade 6. All percentage-computation tasks are marked kind=NONE to indicate this boundary.").

