vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G6-U3-L13', "Every operand in this lesson appears in readable text (pdftotext captured all questions, answers, and the Practice 2 table), so no task event is figure-bound. The lesson's core work is computing benchmark percentages of a quantity and the reverse (finding the whole from a percentage part). Two families fall outside the K-6 automaton set and are tagged NONE: (a) 75% forward and 75%/150% reverse via non-unit fractions — 75% of a quantity multiplies by 3/4, and \"9 is 75%/150% of what number?\" multiplies by 4/3 or 2/3, none of which map to a unit-fraction division or an equal-groups multiplication").

vision_lesson('IM-G6-U3-L14', 6, 3, 14, "Solving Percentage Problems").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U3-L14', teacher, "Choose and create a tape diagram, double number line diagram, or table to solve problems involving percentages and explain (orally) the solution method.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U3-L14', teacher, "Determine what information is needed to solve a problem involving percentages. Ask questions to elicit that information.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U3-L14', student, "Let's solve more percentage problems.").
vision_lesson_purpose('IM-G6-U3-L14', "In this lesson, students solve percentage problems with less scaffolding and engage with all three kinds of questions that are commonly asked in situations where A% of B is C: (1) What is A% of B?; (2) What is B if A% of B is C?; (3) What percentage of B is C?. In the Warm-up, students reason about what percentage one whole number is of another whole number, with most problems involving benchmark percentages. In the main activity, an Info Gap, students practice identifying what information they need to solve percentage problems, asking for that information, and solving the problems. Unlike earlier lessons, no blank representations or intermediate prompts are given, so students must choose approaches that seem appropriate.").
vision_lesson_standard('IM-G6-U3-L14', building_on, '5.NF.B').
vision_lesson_standard('IM-G6-U3-L14', addressing, '6.RP.A.3.c').
