vision_lesson('IM-G6-U4-L10', 6, 4, 10, "Dividing by Unit and Non-Unit Fractions").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U4-L10', teacher, "Interpret and critique explanations (in spoken and written language, as well as in other representations) of how to divide by a fraction.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U4-L10', teacher, "Use a tape diagram to represent dividing by a non-unit fraction a/b and explain (orally) why this produces the same result as multiplying the number by b and dividing by a.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U4-L10', teacher, "Use a tape diagram to represent dividing by a unit fraction 1/b and explain (orally and in writing) why this is the same as multiplying by b.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U4-L10', student, "Let's look for patterns when we divide by a fraction.").
vision_lesson_purpose('IM-G6-U4-L10', "Students use tape diagrams to recall two ideas from grade 5: dividing by a whole number b has the same result as multiplying by the unit fraction 1/b, and dividing by a unit fraction 1/b has the same result as multiplying by the whole number b. They extend the second idea to division by non-unit fractions, seeing it as a two-step process: partition each whole into as many parts as the denominator (multiply by the denominator), then group those parts by the numerator (divide by the numerator). Through repetition they notice a pattern (MP8) and use structure (MP7) so they can find fraction quotients without always drawing diagrams.").
