vision_lesson('IM-G6-U5-L4', 6, 5, 4, "Adding and Subtracting Decimals with Many Non-Zero Digits").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U5-L4', teacher, "Choose a strategy for adding and subtracting decimals efficiently, especially decimals with multiple non-zero digits.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U5-L4', teacher, "Interpret a description (in written language) of a real-world situation involving decimals, and write an addition or subtraction problem to represent it.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U5-L4', teacher, "Use the standard algorithm to add or subtract decimals with multiple non-zero digits, and explain (orally) the solution method.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U5-L4', student, "Let's practice adding and subtracting decimals.").
vision_lesson_purpose('IM-G6-U5-L4', "This lesson strengthens students' ability to add and subtract decimals, enabling them to work toward fluency. Students encounter longer decimals (beyond thousandths), find unknown addends, and work with decimals in context. They decide which operation (addition or subtraction) to perform and which strategy to use. The lesson reinforces that a decimal can be expressed in different but equivalent ways, and that writing additional zeros after the last digit to the right of the decimal point does not change its value. To solve these problems, students must lean on understanding of base-ten numbers and make use of structure (MP7), reasoning abstractly and quantitatively (MP2).").
vision_lesson_standard('IM-G6-U5-L4', addressing, '6.NS.B.3').
