vision_lesson_purpose('IM-G6-U5-L5', "The core lesson operation is decimal multiplication using fractional decomposition and place-value understanding. Students reason from unit fractions (1/10, 1/100, 1/1000) and their decimal equivalents (0.1, 0.01, 0.001), recognize that multiplying by these is equivalent to dividing by 10, 100, and 1,000, then express each decimal factor as a whole number times a power-of-ten fraction and apply the commutative and associative properties to compute products of two decimals.").
