vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G6-U6-L2', "This lesson is about transitioning from evaluating the truth of numerical equations to understanding that equations with variables have truth-values that depend on substituted values. The trickiest misconception: students often conflate an equation being \"true\" with being \"solved\" or think equations with false statements are somehow invalid. They also struggle to distinguish between a variable (a placeholder for any value) and a solution (the specific value or values that make the equation true). No specialized arithmetic strategies beyond substitution are required; the cognitive work is entir").

vision_lesson('IM-G6-U6-L3', 6, 6, 3, "Staying in Balance").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U6-L3', teacher, "I can compare the process of removing or grouping weights to keep a hanger diagram balanced and the process of subtracting or dividing numbers to solve an equation.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U6-L3', teacher, "I can explain what a balanced hanger diagram and a true equation have in common.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U6-L3', teacher, "I can write equations that could represent the weights on a balanced hanger diagram.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U6-L3', student, "Let's use balanced hangers to help us solve equations.").
vision_lesson_purpose('IM-G6-U6-L3', "The goal of this lesson is for students to understand why we can generally approach solving p + x = q by subtracting the same value from each side and why we can generally approach solving px = q by dividing each side by the same value. This understanding is accomplished by considering what can be done to a hanger to keep it balanced. Previously, students solved a variable equation by thinking about values for the variable that made the equation true. Here, they use the image of a balanced hanger to reason about things they could \"do\" to the equation to make the solution easier to see while still keeping both sides of the equation equal (balanced). In the next lesson, students will apply this strategy to solve equations algebraically.").
vision_lesson_standard('IM-G6-U6-L3', addressing, '6.EE.B.5').
vision_lesson_standard('IM-G6-U6-L3', addressing, '6.EE.B.6').
