vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G6-U6-L5', "This lesson challenges students to recognize that different situations embody different structures—additive (parts to whole), multiplicative (scaling), comparative (differences)—and match those structures to equation forms rather than relying on keyword strategies alone. Common pitfall: students select equations based on surface language ('times,' 'altogether') without understanding the actual quantitative relationship, or they solve correctly but fail to interpret the solution in context with appropriate units and meaning.").

