vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U6-L6', teacher, "Use equations to solve problems involving percentages and explain (orally) the solution method.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U6-L6', teacher, "Write equations of the form px = q or equivalent to represent situations where the amount that corresponds to 100% is unknown.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U6-L6', student, "Let's use equations to find percentages.").
vision_lesson_purpose('IM-G6-U6-L6', "In this lesson, students apply what they have learned about solving equations of the form px = q to situations that involve percentages. Students learned about what percentages are and how to solve percentage problems in an earlier unit. However, they did not generalize the reasoning process for finding the value that corresponds to 100% when a percentage and its value is known, or finding B in \"A% of B is C\" given A and C. Students have an opportunity to generalize that process in this lesson.").
