vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G6-U6-L6', "The central challenge is the inverse percentage problem: students can usually find \"what is 40% of 200?\" but struggle with \"if 40% of something is 80, what is it?\" This lesson demands they recognize the equation form p/100·x=q and solve by division or equivalent reasoning. Students frequently reverse operations, forget to account for the percentage as a decimal/fraction, or misidentify which quantity is the 100% reference.").

