vision_lesson('IM-G6-U6-L8', 6, 6, 8, "Equal and Equivalent").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U6-L8', teacher, "Explain (in writing) that some pairs of expressions are equal for one value of their variable but not for other values.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U6-L8', teacher, "Justify (using words or other representations) whether two expressions are \"equivalent,\" or equal to each other for every value of their variable.").
vision_lesson_purpose('IM-G6-U6-L8', "In this lesson, students are introduced to equivalent expressions—expressions that always have the same value. Students begin by using tape diagrams to justify whether two numerical expressions are equal. They then use tape diagrams to represent two expressions with variables when given a value for the variable. Through repeated reasoning, they distinguish between equivalent expressions (which have the same value for all values of the variable) and expressions that may be equal for some but not all values of a variable. Students identify simple equivalent expressions using structure and properties of operations.").
