vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G6-U6-L9', "This problem requires students to apply the triangle area formula A = ½ × base × height to two triangles with different dimensions and compare results. Students often misconceive that a taller height always yields a larger area, or conflate base and height. The problem's value lies in revealing that area depends multiplicatively on both dimensions; a smaller base paired with a moderate height can rival a larger base with a smaller height.").

