vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G6-U7-L15', "Every arithmetic demand in Lesson 15 maps to an automaton: horizontal/vertical segment lengths as axis_aligned_coordinate_distance, perimeters as polygon or rectangle boundary accumulation, rectangle area as rectangle_area_unit_iteration, square-side-from-perimeter as fair_share_equal_groups division, and the two spiral-review decimals in Practice Problem 4 (labeled \"from Unit 6, Lesson 5\") as decimal add/multiply. One operation resists a clean binary task_event: the optional \"Are You Ready for More?\" extension on page 217 asks for the area of Polygon D (19.5 square units), which the solution").

vision_lesson('IM-G6-U7-L16', 6, 7, 16, "Common Factors").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U7-L16', teacher, "Comprehend (orally and in writing) the terms \"factor,\" \"common factor,\" and \"greatest common factor.\"").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U7-L16', teacher, "Explain (orally and in writing) how to determine the greatest common factor of two whole numbers less than 100.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U7-L16', teacher, "List the factors of a number, and identify common factors for two numbers in a real-world situation.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U7-L16', student, "Let's use factors to solve problems.").
vision_lesson_purpose('IM-G6-U7-L16', "In this lesson, students are introduced to common factors of two whole numbers as factors that both numbers share and the greatest common factor as the largest of these shared factors. Students reason abstractly and quantitatively as they see factors as representing different ways to divide a certain number of books evenly (MP2). They make use of structure when they notice how factor pairs help ensure that all possible combinations have been found (MP7). Common factors represent the ways to combine two different types of books in one box, and the greatest common factor represents the largest number of combination boxes possible. Students also relate the greatest common factor to the size of the largest square that can tile a rectangle with given dimensions without gaps or overlaps.").
vision_lesson_standard('IM-G6-U7-L16', addressing, '6.NS.B.4').
