vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G6-U8-L3', "Students frequently confuse when to use dot plots (numerical data on a number line) versus bar graphs (categorical data). Common errors include drawing dots of inconsistent sizes, failing to stack them vertically, or misplacing dots on the number line. Understanding that frequency is shown by stacking dots directly above a value—and that this spatial arrangement reveals the distribution's shape—is foundational to later work on center and spread.").

