vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G6-U8-L5', "This lesson bridges informal and formal understanding of distributions. Students move from descriptive language (typical, spread out) toward identifying center and spread visually in dot plots. The main challenge is that students often fixate on the highest stack of dots (the mode) rather than finding the true center of the overall distribution; they also frequently confuse spread with range rather than understanding spread as concentration or dispersal of points around center.").

vision_lesson('IM-G6-U8-L6', 6, 8, 6, "Interpreting Histograms").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U8-L6', teacher, "Compare and contrast (orally) dot plots and histograms in terms of how useful they are for answering different statistical questions.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U8-L6', teacher, "Create a histogram to represent a data set.").
