vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G6-U8-L6', "Histograms group continuous data into intervals, showing overall distribution patterns while losing precision about individual values. Students often struggle to accept that you cannot determine exact values or specific frequencies from a histogram—only ranges and combined counts—a trade-off that is central to understanding when histograms are more useful than dot plots.").

