vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G6-U8-L8', "Histograms and bar graphs are visually similar but represent different data types. Students struggle to see that histogram features—peaks, gaps, symmetry, clusters—describe the actual data distribution, not just the visual appearance of the graph itself. Distinguishing when to use each representation and interpreting what distribution features reveal about the underlying data takes deliberate practice.").

