vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G6-U8-L10', "This lesson teaches students to write inequalities that capture real-world constraints and to test whether specific values are solutions by both algebraic substitution and contextual reasoning. Students often conflate the algebraic solution set with the feasible set (e.g., treating negative solutions as if they were valid just because they satisfy the inequality mathematically, rather than recognizing that context—no negative quantities of goods—restricts the domain). The dual-representation work (representing the same constraint through both c and m) helps students understand that multiple va").

