vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G6-U8-L17', "Box plots compare distributions by displaying center (median) and spread (IQR) as independent dimensions. Students struggle most with comparing two plots that share one measure but differ in the other—for example, recognizing that the same median does not guarantee similar distributions if the IQRs are very different. They often fail to connect the five-number summary values to the visual box plot representation, or they conflate visual similarity with statistical equivalence.").

