vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U8-L18', teacher, "Recognize that different graphical displays offer different insights into a distribution. Choose an appropriate graphical display to represent a data set, and justify the choice (orally and in writing).").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U8-L18', teacher, "Recognize that different measures of center and variability offer different insights into a data set. Choose an appropriate measure of center and variability to describe a data set, and justify the choice (orally and in writing).").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G6-U8-L18', student, "Let's compare data sets using visual displays.").
vision_lesson_purpose('IM-G6-U8-L18', "This optional lesson is a good opportunity for students to use the information that they have learned in the unit and to apply it to different situations. After reinforcing interpretations of box plots in context, several activity options are available depending on class needs, ranging from analyzing real-world distributions to working with large data sets digitally.").
