vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G7-U1-L5', "Students often think of the scaled copy as always bigger (scale factor > 1) and struggle to visualize what happens when the scale factor is less than 1—a copy that is smaller. A second common misconception: students may not recognize that scale factors are reversible (reciprocal pairs) and think that if Figure B is scaled from A by factor 2, then A cannot also be a scaled copy of B. The lesson's emphasis on classifying scale factors (less than 1, exactly 1, greater than 1) and identifying reciprocals directly addresses both.").

