vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G7-U1-L7', "Students learn to use scale ratios to convert between drawing and actual measurements, but often misunderstand that scales create multiplicative (not additive) relationships and that 2D scale drawings of 3D objects capture only two dimensions. Unit confusion during scale conversion is a frequent error, especially when mixing measurement systems (inches to feet, centimeters to meters).").

