vision_lesson_purpose('IM-G7-U2-L8', "In this lesson, students examine equations of proportional and nonproportional relationships. They use the equation to complete a table of values and then divide the pairs of values on each row to determine whether the relationship is proportional. The focus is on looking for and making use of structure (MP7): connecting the form of the equation to the kind of relationship it represents. The final activity is optional practice without a context, so students attend to the structure of the equations.").
