vision_lesson_standard('IM-G7-U2-L10', addressing, '7.RP.A.2.a').
vision_lesson_standard('IM-G7-U2-L10', building_toward, '7.RP.A.2.a').
vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G7-U2-L10', "This lesson demands geometric and conceptual work, not arithmetic computation. Students plot ordered pairs from pre-given tables on coordinate planes, interpret the resulting graphs, and identify features of proportional relationships (straight line through origin, constant ratio). They answer questions like \"What does x represent?\" and \"What do you notice about the graph?\" — all conceptual or geometric inquiry. The lesson has no tasks asking students to compute quotients, products, sums, or differences. The model has no automata for ordered-pair plotting or proportional-relationship graph int").

