vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G7-U2-L13', "This lesson's primary cognitive demand is identifying and using constants of proportionality by computing y ÷ x from tables and graphs. This ratio-finding operation is not represented in the controlled vocabulary of arithmetic strategies, which focus on K-8 computation (counting, place value, equal groups, etc.). All divisions in this lesson are marked kind=NONE. The lesson works at the algebraic level of proportional reasoning rather than arithmetic strategy selection.").

vision_lesson('IM-G7-U2-L14', 7, 2, 14, "Four Representations").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G7-U2-L14', teacher, "Calculate the constant of proportionality for a proportional relationship in an unfamiliar context, and express it (in writing) using the correct units.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G7-U2-L14', teacher, "Critique (orally and in writing) presentations of proportional and nonproportional relationships.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G7-U2-L14', teacher, "Invent and describe (in writing and using other representations) a proportional relationship and a nonproportional relationship.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G7-U2-L14', student, "Let's contrast relationships that are and are not proportional in four different ways.").
vision_lesson_purpose('IM-G7-U2-L14', "This lesson is optional because it presents an open-ended problem for students to review everything they have learned in this unit. Students invent their own situation that involves a proportional relationship. They represent it using a sentence, a table, an equation, and a graph. As students identify quantities and relationships to represent a situation, they are modeling with mathematics (MP4). Note that the real-world relationship that students choose to represent may not be exactly proportional. In other words, the rate relating the two quantities may involve some variability and is only roughly constant. It is fine for students to approximate an average constant rate in such cases. Discussions of measurement error and statistical variability will be addressed in later units.").
vision_lesson_standard('IM-G7-U2-L14', building_on, '6.RP.A.3').
vision_lesson_standard('IM-G7-U2-L14', addressing, '7.RP.A').
