vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G7-U3-L5', "The core insight is that circumference determines distance per rotation, creating a proportional relationship: total distance = circumference × rotations. Watch for two persistent errors: (1) measurement errors when students roll physical objects in straight lines and mark rotations precisely—this is surprisingly difficult in practice—and (2) unit-conversion mistakes when scaling from rotations to miles, especially converting between inches, feet, and miles. Students often underestimate how many rotations a wheel makes to travel a long distance.").

vision_lesson('IM-G7-U3-L6', 7, 3, 6, "Estimating Areas").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G7-U3-L6', teacher, "Estimate the area of a complex, real-world region, e.g., a state or province, by approximating it with an irregular polygon, and indicate that it is an approximation when expressing the answer (orally and in writing).").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G7-U3-L6', teacher, "Explain (orally and in writing) how to calculate the area of an irregular polygon by decomposing it.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G7-U3-L6', teacher, "Interpret floor plans and maps in order to identify the information needed to calculate area.").
