vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G7-U3-L8', "This lesson makes A = πr² derivable through hands-on dissection and rearrangement, not memorizable in isolation. Students must coordinate three related measurements (radius, circumference, area) and understand that rearranging a shape preserves its area. Common errors: confusing the area formula with circumference, mistaking diameter for radius when computing area, or failing to recognize that the rearranged parallelogram/triangle has the same area as the original circle. Assumes prior knowledge that C = 2πr.").

