vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G7-U3-L11', "Students must coordinate two-dimensional area measurements with one-dimensional perimeter/length measurements to solve a real-world cost problem. The most common error in the scaling activity is assuming the cost simply multiplies by the scale factor, missing that areas scale by the square while lengths scale linearly. The lesson also requires making geometric assumptions (treating curved regions as circle arcs) and handling multi-step calculations without relying on arithmetic fluency—calculators are recommended to keep focus on the modeling and reasoning.").

