vision_lesson_purpose('IM-G7-U4-L9', "In this lesson, students consider how to calculate a fractional percentage using a whole number percentage as a reference. For example, if they know that 1% of 200 is 2, they can use the structure of the base-ten system to reason that 0.1% of 200 is 0.2, and 0.01% of 200 is 0.02 (MP7). First, students use place value and properties of operations to calculate percentages without a context. Next, they apply this reasoning about fractional percentages to situations involving percent increase.").
