vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G7-U4-L9', "Every computational demand maps to an automaton in the vocabulary. Percent-of-a-quantity tasks (of 60, of 5,000, of 80, 3 1/2% of 20, 22.6% of 65) and percent-increase tasks (the two populations, the 750-student cool-down, the 560-pound construction problem) both reduce to decimal_multiplication_rule; the increase tasks apply a 1+r multiplier (1.08, 1.008, 1.04, 1.004, 1.30). The warm-up's division by 100 is captured by recalled_result_scaling: students shift place value and halve prior results (14/100 to 0.14, then 7/100 as half of that). The snack-shop part-of-whole percentages reduce to fai").

