vision_lesson('IM-G7-U5-L6', 7, 5, 6, "Finding Differences").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G7-U5-L6', teacher, "Compare and contrast (orally) subtraction expressions that have the same numbers in the opposite order.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G7-U5-L6', teacher, "Recognize that the 'difference' of two numbers can be positive or negative, depending on the order they are listed, while the 'distance' between two numbers is always positive.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G7-U5-L6', teacher, "Subtract signed numbers, and explain (orally) the reasoning.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G7-U5-L6', student, "Let's bring addition and subtraction together.").
vision_lesson_purpose('IM-G7-U5-L6', "In this lesson, students build fluency with subtracting signed numbers. They learn that \"the difference of a and b\" means a – b. They see that the difference between two numbers can be positive or negative depending on the relative position of the numbers on the number line. For example, 9 − 7 = 2, while 7 − 9 = -2. If students had previously understood subtraction to involve always subtracting the lesser number from the greater number, then this lesson is an opportunity for them to develop a more nuanced understanding of subtraction. As students write subtraction expressions to represent differences in elevation, they are reasoning abstractly and quantitatively (MP2).").
