vision_lesson('IM-G7-U6-L1', 7, 6, 1, "Relationships between Quantities").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G7-U6-L1', teacher, "Determine unknown values in a relationship that is not proportional, and explain (orally and in writing) the solution method.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G7-U6-L1', teacher, "Interpret and describe (orally and in writing) relationships that are predictable, but not proportional.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G7-U6-L1', teacher, "Justify (orally) that a given relationship is not proportional.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G7-U6-L1', student, "Let's try to solve some new kinds of problems.").
vision_lesson_purpose('IM-G7-U6-L1', "In this introductory lesson, students encounter some contexts involving relationships that are not proportional. Students are not expected to write expressions or equations, or use any specific representation for these problems. However, they may choose to make diagrams or tables or reason in some other way. The goal here is to help students see that we need some new strategies to solve these new kinds of problems. It is the work of this unit to develop those strategies.").
