vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G7-U6-L3', "This lesson bridges visual and algebraic thinking by showing how tape diagrams and equations represent the same relationships. Students often fail to recognize that multiple equations can represent one diagram (e.g., 2x + 5 = 19 and 19 = 5 + 2x are equivalent), and they may not connect parentheses in equations to grouping in diagrams (e.g., the structural difference between 2(x + 5) = 19 and 2x + 5 = 19). The lesson intentionally avoids formal solving procedures, asking students to reason through the diagram using intuitive methods—a fundamental departure from rote algorithmic approaches.").

