vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G7-U6-L4', "Students must coordinate three representations—situations, tape diagrams, and equations of the form px + q = r—learning to map diagram parts to equation components. The critical challenge: identifying what the variable represents and how the constant and coefficient show up visually in the tape. This lesson intentionally avoids formal algebraic moves (like \"do the same to both sides\"); instead, it builds reasoning from diagram structure and equation meaning before procedural techniques enter.").

