vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G7-U6-L6', "This lesson helps students distinguish between two structurally different linear equations: one where you multiply a variable then add a constant (px + q = r), and another where you add a constant to a variable then multiply (p(x + q) = r). Students often struggle to match real-world situations to the correct equation form—the lesson uses tape diagrams to make the structure visible and show that equation form reflects the order of actions in a story.").

