vision_lesson_goal('IM-G7-U6-L8', teacher, "Compare and contrast (orally) different strategies for solving an equation of the form p(x + q) = r.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G7-U6-L8', teacher, "Explain (orally and in writing) how to use a balanced hanger diagram to solve an equation of the form p(x + q) = r.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G7-U6-L8', teacher, "Interpret a balanced hanger diagram with multiple groups, and justify (in writing) that there is more than one way to write an equation that represents the relationship shown.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G7-U6-L8', student, "Let's use hangers to understand two different ways of solving equations with parentheses.").
vision_lesson_purpose('IM-G7-U6-L8', "This lesson continues developing efficient equation solving strategies justified by hanger diagrams. Students understand two different ways to solve p(x + q) = r efficiently. After reviewing the distributive property, the first activity explains why either of two equations could represent a diagram. The second activity matches equations to diagrams and solves them. The goal is for students to see and understand two approaches to solving this type of equation.").
