vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G7-U6-L8', "Balanced hangers justify two solution methods for p(x + q) = r: divide by p first, then subtract q; or distribute p first, then solve. Students commonly confuse 2(x + 5) with 2x + 5, misread the hanger as 2 + x instead of 2x, or doubt that both approaches yield the same answer. The concrete hanger grounding is essential to prevent confusion between multiplicative grouping and sequential operations.").

vision_lesson('IM-G7-U6-L9', 7, 6, 9, "Dealing with Negative Numbers").
