vision_lesson_purpose('IM-G7-U6-L9', "Students extend the \"do the same thing to each side\" method to equations involving negative numbers. After a warm-up comparing rational number operations, they solve straightforward equations with negative coefficients and constants, then work with a partner to create equivalent equations by applying sequences of transformations. The central idea: doing the same operation to both sides maintains equality and preserves solutions, even when the moves are counterproductive toward isolation, and even when negative numbers are involved.").
