vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G7-U6-L10', "This lesson teaches two equally valid pathways for solving equations of the form p(x + q) = r: dividing the coefficient into both sides first, or distributing first. The instructional work is not about computing solutions but about recognizing which method is more efficient for specific numbers. Students often fail to see p(x + q) as a single quantity and instead attempt to isolate variables mechanically; they also make errors distributing (forgetting to multiply all terms) or treating fractional results as failures. The lesson's core tension is strategic: a student who can solve the equation").

