vision_lesson('IM-G7-U6-L14', 7, 6, 14, "Distinguishing Proportional from Non-Proportional Linear Relationships; Interpreting and Matching Equations to Contexts").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G7-U6-L14', teacher, "Distinguish proportional relationships (constant unit rate) from non-proportional linear functions (with fixed fees or intercepts)").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G7-U6-L14', teacher, "Interpret real-world situations and match them appropriately to linear equations, recognizing when a simple proportional model fails").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G7-U6-L14', teacher, "Execute signed-integer addition and solve problems requiring symbolic reasoning about linear structures").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G7-U6-L14', student, "Solve problems involving signed integers in sequence contexts; determine whether cost-and-quantity relationships are proportional; identify which word problems can be solved by given linear equations").
vision_lesson_purpose('IM-G7-U6-L14', "This lesson solidifies the critical distinction between proportional and non-proportional linear relationships. Students learn that while both have constant rates of change, only proportional relationships pass through the origin; non-proportional linear functions include fixed costs that make them unsuitable for certain equation forms. Students also practice recognizing when real-world contexts do or do not fit standard equation templates like 3x = 27.").
