vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G7-U6-L19', "This lesson introduces expand and factor as inverse operations using the distributive property, with special emphasis on handling negative coefficients and recognizing variables as common factors. The most frequent errors: students mishandle sign distribution (e.g., -2(3x - 5) becomes -6x - 10 instead of -6x + 10), or fail to recognize when a variable is a common factor (e.g., 3x - 2x = (3 - 2)x). The reasoning students must develop here—that factoring reverses expanding—is foundational for later polynomial work; the formal connection to combining like terms (e.g., 3a + 2a = (3 + 2)a) becomes").

vision_lesson('IM-G7-U6-L20', 7, 6, 20, "Combining Like Terms (Part 1)").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G7-U6-L20', teacher, "Apply properties of operations to justify (orally and in writing) that expressions are equivalent.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G7-U6-L20', teacher, "Generate an expression with fewer terms that is equivalent to a given expression.").
