vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G7-U6-L22', "The core insight is that the order of applying two successive discounts matters—applying the percentage discount first then the fixed amount always saves a fixed $6 more, independent of purchase price. Students typically believe order doesn't matter (Mai's reasoning) or depends on the purchase amount (Kiran's reasoning). The lesson demands algebraic reasoning with expressions and the distributive property to justify a general claim, moving beyond testing specific dollar amounts.").

