vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G7-U7-L1', "Angles measure turn, not ray length—a distinction many students conflate. Students often struggle to internalize why exactly three hexagons fit around a point (their 120° interior angles divide 360° evenly) and why this matters; they also commonly misread protractors or confuse angle names (DAB vs. BAD). The lesson assumes Grade 4 mastery of protractors and basic angle addition.").

