vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G7-U7-L2', "Students frequently confuse complementary (90°) and supplementary (180°) angles, and struggle to identify adjacent angle pairs from diagrams or protractor readings. The core insight—that specific adjacent angle pairs always compose to 90° or 180°—requires first measuring to discover the pattern, then recognizing the relationship as a tool for finding unknowns. Without understanding that adjacency matters, students apply the property incorrectly to non-adjacent angle pairs.").

