vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G7-U7-L12', "This practice page reviews angle relationships at intersecting lines, equivalent algebraic representations of percentage decrease, and linear equation solving. Students often struggle with visualizing angle composition at intersections, recognizing the equivalence of 0.2x, (1-0.8)x, and x - 0.8x as expressions for an 80% decrease, and avoiding procedural errors like subtracting before distributing in equations. Problem 5 explicitly trains error detection through substitution checking.").

