vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G7-U7-L16', "This lesson demands that students distinguish volume (amount of material to fill a 3D space) from surface area (amount to cover the outside), then apply that distinction strategically within real-world constraints. Students frequently confuse which measure applies to a context; the lesson teaches discrimination through problems where both quantities matter for different parts of the solution. Cost calculations then reinforce that volume and surface area scale differently (volume by the cube of a linear scale factor, surface area by the square), requiring students to reconsider their reasoning").

