vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G7-U8-L4', "This lesson teaches theoretical probability using equally likely outcomes and the sample space formula P(event) = 1/n. Students frequently struggle to systematically enumerate ALL outcomes without duplication; the cool-down exploits this by asking them to find letters in weekday names, a non-obvious sample space. Common misconception: confusing the size of the sample space with the probability of an outcome. The lesson is purely formal (theoretical probability based on logical enumeration), not empirical; actual \"repeated experiments\" would belong to a follow-up lesson to test whether observed").

vision_lesson('IM-G7-U8-L5', 7, 8, 5, "More Estimating Probabilities").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G7-U8-L5', teacher, "Describe (orally and in writing) reasons why the relative frequency from an experiment may not exactly match the actual probability of the event.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G7-U8-L5', teacher, "Recognize that sometimes the outcomes in a sample space are not equally likely.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G7-U8-L5', teacher, "Use the results from a repeated experiment to estimate the probability of an event, and justify (orally and in writing) the estimate.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G7-U8-L5', student, "Let's estimate some probabilities.").
vision_lesson_purpose('IM-G7-U8-L5', "In this lesson students compare the results from running actual trials of an experiment to the calculated expected probabilities. They also use their data to see that additional trials usually produce more accurate results as minor differences even out after many trials. In the first activity, students spin four different spinners to see that the outcomes in a sample space may not be equally likely, and they examine the spinners to construct arguments about why some outcomes are more likely than others. In the next activity, students draw blocks out of a bag repeatedly and use the relative frequency to estimate the probability of getting a green block.").
vision_lesson_standard('IM-G7-U8-L5', addressing, '7.SP.C.5').
vision_lesson_standard('IM-G7-U8-L5', addressing, '7.SP.C.6').
