vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G7-U8-L6', "Students use simulations to estimate probabilities of events hard to observe directly, performing many trials, computing cumulative relative frequency, and recognizing that convergence requires substantial data collection. Common misconceptions: treating small samples (3 out of 4 trials) as definitive probability; designing simulations where the simulation outcomes fail to match real-world probabilities; underestimating how many trials are needed to stabilize an estimate.").

