vision_lesson('IM-G7-U8-L8', 7, 8, 8, "Keeping Track of All Possible Outcomes").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G7-U8-L8', teacher, "Interpret or create a list, table, or tree diagram that represents the sample space of a compound event, and use the sample space to write the probability for an event.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G7-U8-L8', teacher, "Describe a multi-step experiment that could be used to simulate a compound event in a real-world situation, and justify that it represents the situation.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G7-U8-L8', student, "Interpret or create a list, table, or tree diagram to represent sample spaces of compound events and use them to calculate probabilities; design and justify simulations of compound probability situations.").
vision_lesson_purpose('IM-G7-U8-L8', "This checkpoint assesses students' ability to enumerate compound sample spaces systematically and apply the probability formula (favorable outcomes / total outcomes). It also evaluates whether students can design valid simulations that accurately represent given probability conditions.").
