vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G7-U8-L8', "Students often fail to enumerate sample spaces completely and systematically—missing outcomes (undercounting to 6 or 8) or double-counting. For the probability calculation, students must locate favorable outcomes from a tree/list structure and apply favorable/total reasoning. The simulation design task (Item 2) requires students to map a 25% game probability to a 50% coin outcome (requires two coins, both heads); students commonly select simulations that don't match the probability structure. Note: CCSS standards and full lesson purpose are not visible on these checkpoint pages; refer to the l").

vision_lesson('IM-G7-U8-L9', 7, 8, 9, "Multi-step Experiments").
