vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G7-U8-L9', "This lesson marks the shift from simple one-step probability to compound (multi-step) experiments. The core work is careful enumeration: students must distinguish that rolling a 2 then a 3 differs from rolling a 3 then a 2, and they must consistently represent all branches (trees, tables, lists). Common pitfalls include undercounting outcomes when dice/coins are involved, confusing \"with replacement\" and \"without replacement\" (the Pick a Card activity), and incorrectly assigning probability to impossible events. Students are also developing the principle that P(event) = (# favorable outcomes)").

vision_lesson('IM-G7-U8-L10', 7, 8, 10, "Designing Simulations").
