vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G7-U8-L14', "This lesson teaches the Law of Large Numbers: experimental probability approaches theoretical probability only after many trials. The central misconception is that students believe small samples (e.g., 10 coin flips) can prove or disprove a theory, or that prior experimental results influence future independent events. Students must work through repeated data collection to experience viscerally that convergence is gradual and uncertain at small sample sizes.").

