vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G7-U8-L20', "Students integrate sampling, probability calculation, and the two-MAD rule for comparing populations. Key struggles: (1) understanding sampling variability—random samples from identical populations naturally yield different statistics, not due to error; (2) misinterpreting the comparison threshold—failing to reach 2 MADs means insufficient evidence of difference, not proof the populations are identical.").

