vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G7-U9-L5', "Fermi problems teach that precision in reporting must match the uncertainty in estimation: reporting a heartbeat count as 524,344,566 falsely suggests certainty when 500,000,000 is honest. Students often struggle to distinguish between exactness and meaningfulness—a number is definitely calculable but should be communicated at an order of magnitude that reflects the simplifying assumptions made.").

vision_lesson('IM-G7-U9-L6', 7, 9, 6, "More Expressions and Equations").
