vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G8-U1-L7', "This lesson's core insight is that rigid transformations (translations, rotations, reflections) preserve all side lengths and angle measures; students must actively measure and compare figures to discover this invariant. Common pitfalls: students may struggle to measure diagonal segments accurately using hand-made rulers or tracing paper, confuse size preservation with position (expecting transformed figures to be in the same location), or believe that rotating or reflecting a figure somehow changes its measurements.").

vision_lesson('IM-G8-U1-L8', 8, 1, 8, "Rotation Patterns").
