vision_lesson_goal('IM-G8-U1-L8', teacher, "Generalize (orally and in writing) the outcome when rotating a line segment 180 degrees.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G8-U1-L8', teacher, "Identify (orally and in writing) the rigid transformations that can build a diagram from one starting figure.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G8-U1-L8', student, "Let's rotate figures in a plane.").
vision_lesson_purpose('IM-G8-U1-L8', "The purpose of this lesson is for students to observe properties of figures that have been rotated 90 degrees or 180 degrees. They generalize that a line segment rotated 180 degrees about a point is either parallel to the original or lies along the same line. They also identify rigid transformations on a triangle involving rotations of multiples of 90 degrees. Students explain that lengths on composite figures must be equal using the property that corresponding side lengths are preserved under rigid transformations.").
