vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G8-U1-L9', "Students observe that parallel lines stay parallel after transformations, but struggle to explain *why* — the conceptual work is understanding that rigid transformations preserve geometric properties. The heart of the lesson is using 180-degree rotations to justify vertical angle congruence; this requires reasoning about how points map to their images and preserving angle measures, not arithmetic. Many students have difficulty visualizing 180-degree rotations dynamically or linking that visualization to the proof of vertical angles.").

vision_lesson('IM-G8-U1-L10', 8, 1, 10, "Composing Figures").
