vision_lesson_goal('IM-G8-U1-L10', teacher, "Generalize that lengths and angle measures are preserved under any rigid transformation").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G8-U1-L10', teacher, "Identify side lengths and angles that have equivalent measurements in composite shapes and explain why they are equivalent").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G8-U1-L10', student, "Let's use reasoning about rigid transformations to find measurements without measuring.").
vision_lesson_purpose('IM-G8-U1-L10', "The purpose of this lesson is for students to apply the property that rigid transformations preserve angle measures and side lengths. Students create composite shapes using translations, rotations, and reflections of polygons and observe that side lengths and angle measures do not change. They apply the property that the image of a line segment under a 180° rotation about a point not on the line is parallel to the original segment to explain why a figure must be a parallelogram. Students use the structure of rigid transformations to apply these properties to various figures.").
vision_lesson_standard('IM-G8-U1-L10', addressing, '8.G.A.1a').
vision_lesson_standard('IM-G8-U1-L10', addressing, '8.G.A.1b').
