vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G8-U1-L12', "Equal corresponding side lengths are necessary but not sufficient for congruence; students commonly overlook that angle measures, side order, and successful rigid transformation sequences all matter. This lesson uses deliberate counterexamples where polygons share identical side lengths but differ in angles or areas, building geometric reasoning (not arithmetic) that congruence demands both matching measurements and a valid transformation sequence.").

vision_lesson('IM-G8-U1-L13', 8, 1, 13, "Congruence").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G8-U1-L13', teacher, "Determine whether shapes are congruent by measuring corresponding points.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G8-U1-L13', teacher, "Draw and label corresponding points on congruent figures.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G8-U1-L13', teacher, "Justify (orally and in writing) that congruent figures have equal corresponding distances between pairs of points.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G8-U1-L13', student, "Let's find ways to test congruence of interesting figures.").
vision_lesson_purpose('IM-G8-U1-L13', "In this lesson, students use rigid transformations and compare features to decide whether shapes with curves are congruent. Unlike polygons, curved shapes may not be defined by a set of vertices, so more care is needed to determine congruence. Students begin the lesson by constructing mathematical questions about an image of ovals, helping them make sense of applying congruence to curved shapes. Students then identify corresponding points on curved figures and compare distances between those points. The focus is that the distance between any pair of corresponding points of congruent figures must be the same. Because there are too many pairs of points to consider, this fact is mainly a criterion for showing that two figures are not congruent—only one example of different distances between pairs of corresponding points is enough to conclude that two figures are not congruent.").
vision_lesson_standard('IM-G8-U1-L13', addressing, '8.G.A.1.a').
vision_lesson_standard('IM-G8-U1-L13', addressing, '8.G.A.2').
