vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G8-U1-L14', "This lesson establishes alternate interior angle congruence via 180° rotation about the midpoint of the transversal segment. The key misconception is that students treat alternate interior angles as congruent by visual appearance or confuse them with corresponding angles, rather than understanding that congruence depends on the lines being parallel and can be justified through rigid transformation.").

vision_lesson('IM-G8-U1-L15', 8, 1, 15, "Adding the Angles in a Triangle").
