vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G8-U3-L1', "This lesson introduces the constant of proportionality (k in y = kx) through two concrete moving objects with different speeds. Students often confuse steepness of a line with speed without attending to the scale of the axes—they may think that because one line is visually steeper, that object must be moving faster, regardless of what the numbers actually show. The lesson's core message is that good graphs require both labels and an appropriate scale to communicate relationships clearly; students frequently omit these conventions.\"").

