vision_lesson_goal('IM-G8-U3-L15', teacher, "Interpret the graph of a linear equation in context, including slope, intercept, and solution, in contexts using multiple representations of non-proportional linear relationships.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G8-U3-L15', teacher, "Write linear equations to reason about real-world situations.").
vision_lesson_purpose('IM-G8-U3-L15', "In this culminating lesson for the unit, students interpret representations of linear relationships in real-world contexts. They study graphs representing linear situations, encountering lines with positive, negative, and zero slopes graphed on the same set of axes for the first time. Students work with equations in both y = mx + b and Ax + By = C formats, identifying situations when one form provides more contextual information. Students solidify what it means to be a solution to an equation by substituting values or checking whether points lie on or off the line.").
