vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G8-U4-L3', "This lesson bridges concrete hanger reasoning to abstract algebraic moves by requiring students to recognize that the same operation on both sides preserves equality—the foundational principle of equation solving. Students often struggle to choose efficiently among multiple valid strategies (distribute first versus divide first), and may not yet see that different paths all yield the same solution.").

