vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G8-U5-L2', "This lesson is primarily conceptual and linguistic, asking students to identify, classify, and describe functions using precise language rather than perform arithmetic. The central misconception is conflating \"multiple inputs map to the same output\" (which is allowed) with \"the same input producing multiple outputs\" (which violates the function definition). Students also often fail to recognize that restricting domain affects which pairs of numbers can be inputs—for instance, -6 cannot be the side length of a geometric figure, so certain function rules become invalid at negative inputs.").

