vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G8-U5-L3', "Many students confuse which variable is independent versus dependent, or assume either variable in a relationship can serve as the input. The lesson clarifies that some relationships allow choice—you can ask \"dimes as a function of quarters\" or vice versa—while others do not, because some functions fail the reversal test: squaring has one output per input, but taking a square root does not have a unique output (both 4 and −4 square to 16).").

