vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G8-U5-L4', "The critical conceptual shift in this lesson is recognizing that the choice of which variable is independent and which is dependent determines whether a relationship is a function. Students often misclassify non-functions as functions by failing to apply the vertical line test correctly, especially when context is present. The lesson's central struggle: a relationship can fail the function test in one direction (e.g., time is not a function of distance when you run around a track and return) but satisfy it in the other (distance IS a function of time). Understanding this context-dependence and").

vision_lesson('IM-G8-U5-L5', 8, 5, 5, "More Graphs of Functions").
