vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G8-U5-L8', "Students learn to represent linear functions with equations y = mx + b, where m is the rate of change and b is the initial value (y-intercept). The main conceptual stumbling block: students often reverse independent and dependent variables or confuse the meaning of m and b in context. They may also assume a negative y-intercept means the function is decreasing, when the direction depends on the sign of the slope (m), not the intercept.").

