vision_lesson_purpose('IM-G8-U5-L9', "In this lesson, students use linear functions to model real-world situations. They develop linear models from data, make predictions, and discuss the reasonableness of their models. Students encounter situations where linear models fail (moon illumination) or only work within bounded intervals (garbage recycling), developing critical judgment about when linear functions are appropriate approximations and what restrictions the model requires.").
