vision_lesson_purpose('IM-G8-U5-L10', "This lesson builds on prior work with linear models for data. In some situations where we wish to quantify change, we want to use different constant rates over different time intervals, so we can model the situation with a piecewise linear function. Students look at temperature data, which change at different rates throughout the day. The rates for these intervals are almost constant. They also use piecewise linear graphs to find information about real-life situations. The focus is to study the graphs qualitatively and compute and compare different rates of change, rather than necessarily finding equations for the piecewise linear functions.").
