vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G8-U5-L12', "Students often read slope values correctly from a graph but fail to connect the number to what it means in context. The key conceptual leap—recognizing that a slope of −1 encodes an inverse trade-off under a binding constraint (fixed perimeter)—requires translating between the abstract slope and the concrete quantities. Watch for students who state \"−1\" without connecting it to the rectangle constraint, or who reason that \"negative slope means the line goes down\" rather than \"width and length are inversely related under fixed perimeter.\"").

