vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G8-U5-L16', "Students work backward from cone volume to find missing dimensions, which requires solving equations involving π and fractions—especially the 1/3 coefficient that expresses why cone volume is one-third of a cylinder's. The main stumbling block is keeping track of which dimension is unknown and managing the algebra; students should anchor to the warm-up fraction strategies (27 = 1/3 h) and recognize that the cone formula V = 1/3 πr²h has the same structure as the cylinder formula, just divided by 3.").

