vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G8-U5-L17', "This lesson establishes that volume is a linear function of one dimension (height or edge length) when other dimensions are held fixed. The core reasoning is proportional: when you scale a dimension by factor k, volume scales by the same factor k. Students typically struggle to explain WHY this happens geometrically, treating it as a memorized pattern rather than as a consequence of the volume formula structure.").

