vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G8-U5-L18', "The critical insight is that when two linear dimensions scale by factor a, volume scales by a². Students often assume volume scales linearly (doubling dimensions doubles volume), missing the quadratic relationship. This manifests as confusion when reading or constructing nonlinear function graphs: the volume curves upward because it depends on the square of the radius or edge length, unlike the linear relationship between height and volume. This lesson is beyond typical Grade 8 scope and requires fluency with squaring, substitution into quadratic expressions, and interpretation of nonlinear gr").

vision_lesson('IM-G8-U5-L19', 8, 5, 19, "Estimating a Hemisphere").
