vision_lesson('IM-G8-U5-L20', 8, 5, 20, "The Volume of a Sphere").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G8-U5-L20', teacher, "Calculate the volume of a sphere, cylinder, and cone which all have a radius of r and height of 2r, and explain (orally) the relationship between their volumes.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G8-U5-L20', teacher, "Create an equation to represent the volume of a sphere as a function of its radius, and explain (orally and in writing) the reasoning.").
vision_lesson_purpose('IM-G8-U5-L20', "Students recognize that the volume of a sphere with radius r is 4/3 πr³ through a visual demonstration in which a sphere fits snugly inside a cylinder (same radius, height equals diameter), and a cone with matching base and height pours into the remaining space. By observing that the sphere and cone together fill the cylinder, students compute volumes and reason about the relationship, then derive the general formula algebraically by manipulating the volume expressions for related solids.").
vision_lesson_standard('IM-G8-U5-L20', addressing, '8.G.C').
vision_lesson_standard('IM-G8-U5-L20', addressing, '8.G.C.9').
