vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G8-U5-L20', "This lesson moves from concrete observation (sphere inside cylinder with cone filling the gap) to the abstract formula V = (4/3)πr³. The core challenge: students see only one specific demonstration yet must believe the ratio holds for all spheres. Common confusion arises when students treat the two computational approaches (using the 2/3 ratio directly vs. subtracting cylinder minus cone) as separate facts rather than equivalent expressions, and when they struggle to understand why a sphere volume formula derived from one physical case generalizes to all spheres. The lesson also requires stude").

