vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G8-U5-L21', "This lesson introduces the sphere volume formula (V = 4/3 πr³) and applies it to solve problems. The most common errors are using r² instead of r³, forgetting to include π as a factor, or confusing the sphere formula with cylinder/cone formulas. The lesson's central challenge—the Information Gap activity—pushes students beyond rote formula application toward mathematical reasoning about which dimensions are sufficient to determine volume, requiring them to ask precise questions about unknown measurements.").

