vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G8-U7-L3', "The critical student confusion here is distinguishing between the product rule (10^m · 10^n = 10^(m+n), where exponents add) and the power rule ((10^n)^m = 10^(n·m), where exponents multiply). The lesson explicitly addresses this in the Lesson Synthesis using 10² · 10² · 10² as a bridge case. Students must grasp that (10^n)^m means m *groups* of n factors each—a counting problem—not addition or concatenation of exponents.").

