vision_lesson_goal('IM-G8-U7-L4', teacher, "Generalize a process for dividing powers of 10, and justify (orally and in writing) that 10^n/10^m = 10^(n-m).").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G8-U7-L4', teacher, "Use exponent rules to multiply and divide with 10^0, and justify (orally) that 10^0 is 1.").
vision_lesson_goal('IM-G8-U7-L4', student, "Let's explore patterns with exponents when we divide powers of 10.").
vision_lesson_purpose('IM-G8-U7-L4', "In this lesson, students continue to make use of repeated reasoning to discover the exponent rule 10^n/10^m = 10^(n-m). Students begin by examining different ways to write fractions that are equivalent to 1. Next, they expand expressions written as the division of two powers of 10 and notice patterns when asked to write the quotient using a single power of 10. Students extend this rule to see what happens when dividing by a value with an exponent of 0, and make sense of why 10^0 is defined to equal 1.").
