vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G8-U7-L5', "This lesson teaches that negative exponents represent repeated division by 10 (equivalently, 10^-n = 1/10^n), grounded in place-value patterns: each step down in exponent multiplies the value by 1/10. The central persistent confusion is distinguishing 10^-5 (a small positive decimal like 0.00001) from -10^5 (a large negative number like -100,000); explicit treatment of where the negative sign lives—in the exponent versus as a sign of the result—is load-bearing.").

