vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G8-U8-L2', "The core conceptual shift is working backward: from area to side length, not forward. Students often believe that if an area falls halfway between two perfect squares, the side length is also halfway between—but squaring is nonlinear. The lesson builds intuition through careful comparison and estimation before formalizing the square root symbol. Students commonly struggle with irrational side lengths (like √29) that do not land neatly on a grid; the tracing-paper verification and circle-rotation construction help make this intuition concrete.").

