vision_lesson_purpose('IM-G8-U8-L3', "In this lesson students use different strategies to approximate the value of square roots when a drawn square is not given. Students begin by finding the areas of tilted squares, writing their exact side lengths, and approximating those side lengths using tracing paper. Next, they create a table and graph of side lengths and areas and use them to verify the accuracy of their tracing paper estimates. Lastly, students work in pairs to find the areas of two squares with an area of 50 square units, requiring them to express the side length as √50.").
