vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G8-U8-L5', "This practice problem surfaces a critical misunderstanding: students often conflate the negative sign as applying to the base (making −1/1,000,000) rather than to the exponent. The task demands fluency with three equivalent representations of negative exponents—fractional form, reciprocal power form, and expanded product form—and depends on understanding that a negative exponent denotes a reciprocal, not a negative quantity. This is the bridge between exponent rules (product and quotient rules) and working with reciprocals in algebraic expressions.").

