vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G8-U8-L7', "The lesson is fundamentally about discovering that for right triangles only, the sum of the squares of the two legs equals the square of the hypotenuse. Students most often confuse the formula's scope (applying it to non-right triangles) and make computational errors: confusing exponents with multiplication by 2, or adding side lengths before squaring rather than squaring first then summing. The lesson explicitly teaches identification of legs versus hypotenuse and emphasizes the relationship holds only for right triangles.").

