vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G8-U8-L10', "This lesson introduces the Pythagorean Theorem as both an algebraic formula and a geometric principle. Students frequently confuse the theorem's application to right triangles only, incorrectly apply it to any triangle, and treat it mechanically without understanding why a² + b² = c² represents a meaningful geometric relationship. The area-based proof requires students to connect algebraic manipulation to visual decomposition, which many find conceptually challenging.").

