vision_lesson_boundary('IM-G8-U8-L15', "This lesson bridges the geometric understanding of cube roots (edge lengths of cubes) to the algebraic understanding (solutions to equations x³ = n). The central challenge for students is distinguishing cube roots from square roots—a confusion the lesson surfaces in Activity 15.4—and learning to approximate irrational cube roots using perfect cubes as reference points on a number line. Most students have no automaton for this yet: reasoning about cube roots requires them to treat the inverse relationship (if x³ = n, then x = ∛n) as conceptually present rather than algorithmically computed.").

